# UnrealTalent — workspace rules

Read **`AGENTS.md`** for full checklists. Non‑negotiables:

## Structure

- **`src/pages/`:** routes only; pass **`BaseLayout`** SEO props (`title`, `description`, optional `ogImagePath`, `robots`, `canonicalPath`, `twitterSite`).
- **`src/layouts/`:** document shell, skip link, global head SEO.
- **`src/components/`:** reusable UI; use **`Button.astro`** for styled actions unless a raw native control is explicitly required.
- **`public/`:** static assets; **no** `robots.txt` (use **`src/pages/robots.txt.ts`**).

## Production SEO

- Set **`PUBLIC_SITE_URL`** at build so **`@astrojs/sitemap`**, **canonical**, **absolute OG**, and **robots Sitemap** line emit.
- Unique **`title`** + **`meta description`** per indexable page; **`noindex`** for non-public pages via **`robots`** prop.
- Add **`ogImagePath`** (1200×630-style asset) when a share image exists; otherwise accept **`summary`** card without image.

## Accessibility

- **`main id="main-content"`** on every page; **skip link** stays first interactive affordance in tab order (after address bar).
- Native **`button` / `a`** for actions; **44×44px** minimum targets for primary controls; **`aria-label`** for icon-only.
- Respect **`prefers-reduced-motion`**; user **Accessibility options** panel sets **`data-ut-*`** on `<html>` — keep that contract stable.

## Commands

- Run **`npm run build`** with **`PUBLIC_SITE_URL`** set before treating SEO work as done.
